#1  Write a program that receives an integer an input. If a string is entered instead of an integer, then report an error and give another chance to user to enter an integer. Continue this process till correct input is supplied.

while True:
    user_input = input("Please enter an integer: ")
    try:
        number = int(user_input)
        print("You entered:", number)
        break
    except ValueError:
        print("That was not an integer. Please try again.")
